Full Job Description

The Architect will report directly to the Director of Design & Engineering. The position encompasses a variety of responsibilities relating to engineering, design, research and interfacing with vendors as well as clients as outlined in detail below.

This position will fall under A/Z Corporation, a Cianbro company. A/Z is an industry-leading, construction and maintenance services provider. Our mission is to provide the highest levels of quality and value to the clients we support in technology-driven industries.

A/Z Corporation’s headquarters is located in North Stonington, CT with satellite locations in MA, NJ and RI. However, the right candidate will have the option to work from any of the Cianbro Companies Maine fixed based offices (Brewer, Pittsfield, Portland or Falmouth) or Baltimore, Maryland fixed based location. If preferred, the candidate will also have the option to relocate to CT, MA, NJ, or RI. This role offers a flexible work schedule with the ability to work from home a couple days per week.

Role & Responsibilities

This position is responsible for design development as it pertains to new construction, renovations, alterations, modifications and design-assist opportunities. This includes schematic design, conceptual design, detailed design development and construction document generation phases;
Provide stamped drawings for worked performed on behalf of A/Z consistent with the Professional Code of Conduct for Architects. In turn, A/Z will indemnify you for work performed under your applicable licenses;
Ensure that proposed designs match client objectives, are functional, aesthetically pleasing, safe and cost effective;
Prepare design presentations and coordinate design development workshops with clients;
Provide support and technical review with other design professionals, consultants, surveyors, engineers, etc. in the production of drawings and specifications;
Preparing applications and assist in the approval process for regulatory planning, zoning, wetland, building departments, or for any Agencies Having Jurisdiction (AHJ’s);
Work with our team to review existing drawings, and provide architectural review in support of advising the client on the practicality of their project;
Perform design optimization reviews of associated assemblies, systems and components that are integral to the project success and life-cycle sustainability considerations;
Support the specifying of mock-up requirements for product quality and finish levels required;
Perform regular site visits to check on progress and product quality in the deployment of construction;
Research and analyze customer design requirements and associated performance data to evaluate the feasibility, design considerations, probable cost, operability and maintenance requirements of designs or applications;
Interface with outside vendors for best components or system selections as it pertains to the application requirements which ensure conformance with design and performance specifications;
Implement and participate in Green Building Design & Construction practices as recognized by industry recognized associations such as USGBC and LEED Accreditation;
Support and perform building code analysis and detailed design development that is consistent with industry best practices, OEM requirements, and any specific technical standards;
Obtain operational proficiency of the latest in design software solutions with computer-assisted design/drafting (CAD 2D / 3D modeling within a BIM environment) and clash detection applications (i.e. Revit, AutoCad, Navisworks, QuickPen, etc.);
Application and understanding of Company design formatting, indexing, reporting and document quality assurance procedures and policies;
Participate in required peer reviews with project team members providing insight and confirmation regarding design completeness, code compliance, constructability evaluations, alternative means and methods, and scope of service definition for associated qualifications, clarifications, and conditions;
Adherence to Corporate Environmental, Health, and Safety Policies and best-practices in the deployment of all work related activities;
Quality control accountability to ensure field compliance with all associated project specifications and technical requirements;
Provide the necessary project information for an organized and controlled project approach;
Maintain all Corporate Standards with applicable Project Control requirements to ensure financial and administrative responsibility, in conjunction with risk management. All project documentation shall be in accordance to the associated master contract terms and conditions;
Provide project finance management for all applicable project commitments, contract changes, and claim resolution for all out-of-scope services to be performed in accordance with Corporate Standards;
Coordinate and support all project close-out, start-up and training in accordance with facility management best practice standards and technical requirements that are outlined within the project performance specifications;
Provide a pro-active and positive Client interface throughout the delivery of services;
Assist in the business development efforts of the Corporation including preconstruction, tactical approaches with project delivery, ensuring a customer-centric focus, client interaction, and presentation assistance;
Initiate continuous improvement objectives and embrace technology enhancements;
Promote, foster and maintain open communication among all project team members, consultants, inspectors, applicable agencies, and the supporting subcontractors and trade participants;
Participation in lessons learned sessions, operational development initiatives, and best practice training to support a continuous improvement working philosophy.

Cianbro is an employee-owned, tobacco-free, equal opportunity employer, we do not discriminate based on marital status, race, color, creed, gender, sex, religion, national origin, gender identity, age, veteran status, union affiliation, physical or mental disability, citizenship status, sexual orientation, genetic information, or other legally protected status.

